{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH85JDGHVuC5XjUWQZzu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. All 3 tests pass.\n\n**Root cause:** In `src/userService.js`, the cache key was `users:${opts.team}` — it left out `includeArchived`. When any caller requested a team's archived-inclusive list (`includeArchived: true`), the result got cached under the plain team key. A subsequent picker request for the same team with `includeArchived: false` hit that cached entry and got archived users back, even though it never asked for them. The 60s cache TTL is why refreshing after a minute cleared it.\n\n**Fix:** Include the archived flag in the cache key so the two request shapes cache separately:\n\n```js\nconst key = `users:${opts.team}:${opts.includeArchived ? \"all\" : \"active\"}`;\n```\n\nI also added `test/userService.test.js` with a regression test for the leak plus one confirming caching still works within a matching key."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":338,"cache_read_input_tokens":23995,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":338},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"29b154a4-a59c-4872-ac33-d702244c7eb0","uuid":"b20b13f0-4f16-4abe-b6ce-02c927b45afd","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:48:51.842Z","request_id":"req_011CdH85EJ7maxtAi8h5dQzr"}
